wc - reads standard input and generates newline count, word count and byte count

wc -l file 
    print the line counts

wc -c file
    print the byte counts

wc -w file 
    prints the word counts

ls -l | wc -l
    prints the number of folders in the directory

grep keyword | wc -l
    prints number of instances the keyword appears in the documents
    for instance *grep prints | wc -l*
    lists the number of instances the word prints appears in the file
